    <h2>6.3.6 Extinction</h2>
    <p>
        - Extinctions occur when there are no remaining individuals of a species still alive.<br>
        - Extinction can be caused by:
        <ul>
            <li>changes in the environment that are too fast (e.g. climate change, habitat destruction)</li>
            <li>the extinction of a species' food source</li>
            <li>the introduction of a new predator or competitor</li>
            <li>new diseases</li>
            <li>invasive species that outcompete</li>
            <li>overpopulation</li>
            <li>over-hunting / over-fishing</li>
            <li>lack of genetic diversity</li>
            <li>natural disasters</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    
